Troubleshooting
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'umap'
The package name is umap-learn, not umap. Make sure you installed from requirements.txt.
bashpip install umap-learn
FileNotFoundError: data/raw/...
Data files are not present. Follow DATA.md to download them first.
UMAP takes too long
If the dataset is large, pass --sample N to visualize.py to subsample N windows for the embedding:
bashpython src/visualize.py --sample 5000
Results differ slightly from the paper
Small differences in accuracy (~1–2%) can occur due to PhysioNet data version, OS-level floating-point behavior, or library updates. The ranking of approaches (multimodal > oximetry > respiratory) should be stable.
